refplat-images-docker (0.3.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Open source compliance (CMLDEV-1123)
    - chrome: switch from proprietary Google Chrome to Debian Chromium;
      drop bundled Google APT signing key and apt-transport-https
      dependency; track chromium package version dynamically from the
      Debian Trixie repository; update node definition UI label and
      description accordingly
    - Remove the netflow container entirely; flow-tools only ships in
      Debian Buster (archived) and the container had been disabled since
      0.1.5

 -- Tomas Mikuska <tmikuska@cisco.com>  Fri, 15 May 2026 19:55:00 +0200

refplat-images-docker (0.3.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * CML 2.10 alignment: docker_tag moves to image definitions
    - Remove "image" from config.json across all node definitions; the
      runtime already prefers the image definition value when present
    - Add docker_tag field to the image definition template
    - Hardcode ui.description to version-less strings
    - Standardize ISO naming to refplat-<YYYYMMDD>-<type>.iso (date-only
      timestamp); update iso-name files to bare names (browser, splunk,
      xrd)
    - Extract SHA256 from the saved tarball manifest instead of
      `docker image inspect` to avoid storage-driver-dependent mismatches
      between CI and CML hosts
    - Fix build.yml container discovery path; drop redundant
      upload-artifact steps from iso-release.yml (releases use assets)

  * Container fixes and defaults
    - chrome / firefox: default RAM raised to 4096
    - firefox: proper dbus socket setup
    - freeRADIUS: capitalization fix (FreeRadius -> FreeRADIUS),
      simplified configuration
    - net-tools, frr: normalize Linux capability names (no CAP_ prefix)
    - thousandeyes: explicit reference tag passed to latest.sh
    - snort: drop caps (NET_ADMIN handled via day0, NET_RAW is in
      Docker's default set)
    - splunk, dnsmasq, frr: misc tidy-ups

  * Build / CI
    - templates/build.mk: add --network host to buildx (matches build
      environment)
    - scripts/latest.sh: accept a reference tag parameter (default
      "latest") and filter out bare hex digests that broke Splunk version
      resolution
    - .github/workflows/release.yml: import GPG signing key without
      requiring a passphrase (Ralph)
    - .gitignore: track per-container metadata.json

 -- Tomas Mikuska <tmikuska@cisco.com>  Thu, 07 May 2026 10:14:31 +0200

