refplat-images-docker (0.1.9) unstable; urgency=medium
  * ISO Release Workflow and Build Improvements
    - Added split ISO build support via make iso, make iso-list, and make clean-iso
    - Introduced scripts/build-split-isos.sh to stage files and create ISOs with xorriso
    - Refactored top-level Makefile to use centralized PKG and parameterized image paths
    - Centralized PKG definition in templates/pkg.mk; included from root and submodule builds
    - Improved build templates: safer command concatenation, portable sed usage, and explicit -follow-links
    - Adjusted module Makefiles (e.g., ThousandEyes, XRd) to align with refactored build and image preparation overrides
    - Updated CI workflow iso-release.yml to accommodate ISO build/release flow

  * Cleanup & update
    - renamed templates/makefile to templates/build.mk
    - extracted clean targets into sub-makefile
    - updated Thousandeyes version

 -- Ralph Schmieder <rschmied@cisco.com>  Wed, 22 Oct 2025 18:34:04 +0200

refplat-images-docker (0.1.8) unstable; urgency=medium

  * CI / release: workflow guard and logging
    - Run metadata guard only for downstream `workflow_run` events to avoid
    unnecessary checks on tag/manual runs
    - Add explicit log steps for tag pushes and manual `workflow_dispatch`
    runs for clearer diagnostics and accurate logging
    - Install `jq` with `DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive` and
    `--no-install-recommends`; clean apt lists and documentation paths to
    reduce runner bloat
    - Prefer the pushed git tag when creating Releases; implement a robust
    tag-selection order and sanity checks to avoid malformed `tag_name` errors

  * Automation: tagging helper
    - Added `tag-release.sh` to help select a successful `build.yml` run and
    create an annotated (optionally signed) tag that points at the built
    commit

  * Documentation
    - Added `TAGGING.md` describing how to create tags that match CI build
    runs
    - Added `VERIFICATION.md` with instructions for importing the project
    public key and verifying detached GPG signatures for release artifacts

 -- Ralph Schmieder <rschmied@cisco.com>  Tue, 14 Oct 2025 12:38:50 +0200

refplat-images-docker (0.1.7) unstable; urgency=medium

  * CI / release: split workflows and signing improvements
    - Split build and release workflows: build job produces artifacts; release
    job downloads, signs, and publishes them
    - Import GPG key and create detached ASCII signatures for artifacts
    (*.asc); attempt Debian-style signing of .changes with debsign
    - Ensure gh CLI is available and use `gh release upload` to attach
    multiple files, including signatures
    - Upload artifacts and signatures to GitHub Release; improved artifact
    upload robustness and metadata handling
  * Build metadata
    - Restore timestamp (ts) in build-metadata.json for traceability
  * Packaging
    - Fixed changelog formatting to comply with dpkg tools

